pullRequest.body:
In this PR, we show that every element `x` of the Witt vectors `ùïé R` can be written as the (`p`-adic) summation of the Teichmuller series. Instead of using `tsum`, we only show that `p ^ (n + 1)` divides `x` minus the summation of the first `n + 1` terms of the Teichmuller series. We also show that if `p` divides the first (n + 1) coefficients of a Witt vector, then `p^(n+1)` divides the `n`-th ghost component.

#21564 depends on this PR.

---

* The `relative` value is the weighted *sum* of the differences with weight given by the *inverse* of the current value of the statistic.
* The `absolute` value is the `relative` value divided by the total sum of the inverses of the current values (i.e. the weighted *average* of the differences).
</details>
Do we really need those? I mean, nothing against them, but if we add them for `RingEquiv` we should do the same for all other equivs.

I believe we need these lemmas, especially those tagged with `[simp]`. Currently, the simp normal form will stop at `(1 : R ‚âÉ+* R) x` without any lemma that can further modify the proof state.

I'll add similar lemmas for other equivs in another PR.

It seems the corresponding lemmas already exist for `MulAut` and `AddAut`. see [MulAut.one_def](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Group/End.html#MulAut.one_def), [MulAut.coe_one](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Group/End.html#MulAut.coe_one)

`AlgAut` doesn't exist yet.

I'll check more and open the PR for aut lemmas later.

```suggestion
@[simp]
theorem iterate_frobeniusEquiv_symm_pow_p_pow (x : R) (n : ‚Ñï) :
    ((frobeniusEquiv R p).symm ^[n]) x ^ (p ^ n) = x := by
  induction n generalizing x with
  | zero => simp
  | succ n ih => simp [pow_succ, pow_mul, ih]
```
`R` is already in scope, and you can use `induction n generalizing x`.

```suggestion
variable (R) in
@[simp]
theorem map_id : WittVector.map (RingHom.id R) = RingHom.id (ùïé R) := by
  ext; simp

theorem map_eq_zero_iff (f : R ‚Üí+* S) {x : WittVector p R} :
    ((map f) x) = 0 ‚Üî ‚àÄ n, f (x.coeff n) = 0 := by
  refine ‚ü®fun h n ‚Ü¶ ?_, fun h ‚Ü¶ ?_‚ü©
  ¬∑ apply_fun (¬∑.coeff n) at h
    simpa using h
  ¬∑ ext n
    simpa using h n
```

```suggestion
  rw [this, show n + 1 = (n - i) + 1 + i by omega, pow_add, mul_comm]
```
Can you add a `variable {R : Type*} ...` line?

```suggestion
    rw [Finset.sum_congr rfl (g := g)]
    ¬∑ simp [g]
```
It looks nicer to me, but not very important.

```suggestion
    rw [‚Üê of_not_not ((teichmuller_mul_pow_coeff_of_ne _).mt ha)]
    exact of_not_not ((teichmuller_mul_pow_coeff_of_ne _).mt hb)
```
